What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The data contains 183412 rows & 16 columns initially. After cleaning the rows are down to 171422 and the columns are up to 22. The data provided information on bike's id, stations' id and location, duration for each ride, and customer's information.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

My area of focus will be the duration of the rides!

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

start time columns. member_birth_year, member_age. member_gender. user_type

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

I found that there is a relation between the number of bike rides and the days where certain days of the week have more bike traffic than others. There is also trend toward starting the bikes either at the early morning (8 o'colck) or the evening (5 o'clock) which is obvoiusly related to working schedules. Also there is the fact that people strongly tend to subscribe than just being casual customer.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

The age of the customers didn't consider the fact that some people will be dead by the year 2019 that's why I got a biker's age of 141, therefore I had to clip the data to include only people less than 60 years old.
